<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
Formerly called <a title="Bible Paper" href="Bible_Paper">bible paper</a>, lightweight papers include a variety of different types of low-thickness, high-<a title="Opacity" href="Opacity">opacity</a> papers used in bibles, handbooks, dictionaries, encyclopedias, and other uses that require low bulk or low weight (for example, in material that will be mailed). The <a title="Basic Size" href="Basic_Size">basic size</a> of lightweight papers is 25 x 38 in., and comes in <a title="Basis Weight" href="Basis_Weight">basis weight</a>s of 17:40 pound. 
</p>
